I found my eyes full of tears at the end of this flow practice. This time last year I was unable to function due to anxiety and depression. I felt isolated and hopeless and couldn't find joy in anything. A year later, thanks to a whole heap of things - finally seeing a counsellor, opening up to my friends and family about my mental health, meditation... I won't bore you all with everything, but I've been doing YWA everyday since April and it's put me more in touch with myself than I've ever been. My self-acceptance and self-love have sky-rocketed, and I'm so filled with gratitude for Adriene and for myself, too.  Thank you <3

Today's session felt meant to be, in a way. It's 17 minutes long and it's the 7th video of the series, and as I practice this day it also happens to be my birthday, the 17th day of the 7th month... This type of quick paced vinyasa flow is what I look forward to while going through Adriene's yoga series. I love the slow hatha movements but most of all I love to flow quickly, and with the breath. What a great way to start the day <3 sending you all love!

I was "supposed" to be on day 18 today, since I started this journey on 6th of April, but due to my poor mental and then physical state I just wasn't able to follow this journey and I took a few days off or did another of your videos (thank you for these for PMS and back pain, and for depression, every each of them helped A LOT!). I was thinking about quitting it completely or starting it all over again, but honestly who cares if it takes 30 days or 100 days? it's my journey! so here i am, day 7, not 1, not no day, day 7, feel like in heaven, haha! Also, thank you for the words "welcome back" at the beggining, I really needed to hear that. I absolutely adore this feeling of kindness and connection, and warmth, and feeling of being important and valid that you gave me, Adriene. I feel like I am always welcome to my mat with you regardless my mental/physical state. I feel like you are my best friend somehow. Thank you. I love you. Thank you to every person in this community for your kindness and loving words. I always read the comment section and it gives me so much love. And finally, thank YOU, anonymous reader, for reading this, if you're still doing it, haha. Love you all, namaste! <3
